## Implementation Plan

### Background

Issue #59 (unwrapResult discards Link headers) and Issue #60 (missing cursor
param in OpenAPI spec) were both addressed by getsentry/sentry#109642 (merged
2026-03-02), which added CursorQueryParam to 19 paginated OpenAPI schemas.
This was regenerated into @sentry/api@0.21.0 (published same day).

### Workaround inventory (pre-fix)

| Function            | Approach               | Reason bypassed SDK                      |
|---------------------|------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| listTeamsPaginated  | orgScopedRequestPaginated (raw HTTP) | SDK Link header issue (#59)  |
| listProjectsPaginated | orgScopedRequestPaginated (raw HTTP) | SDK Link header issue (#59) |
| listRepositoriesPaginated | orgScopedRequestPaginated (raw HTTP) | No cursor in spec (#60) + Link header (#59) |
| listProjects        | orgScopedPaginateAll → orgScopedRequestPaginated | Built atop paginated workaround |
| listRepositories    | apiRequestToRegion (raw HTTP) | SDK had query?: never for repos |
| listIssuesPaginated | SDK + unwrapPaginatedResult | Already migrated previously |

### Steps

1. Upgrade @sentry/api from ^0.1.0 to ^0.21.0
2. Migrate 3 paginated functions to SDK + unwrapPaginatedResult:
   - listTeamsPaginated → listAnOrganization_sTeams
   - listProjectsPaginated → listAnOrganization_sProjects
   - listRepositoriesPaginated → listAnOrganization_sRepositories
3. Migrate 2 non-paginated functions to SDK:
   - listProjects → SDK loop with listAnOrganization_sProjects
   - listRepositories → listAnOrganization_sRepositories + unwrapResult
4. Remove dead raw-HTTP pagination infrastructure:
   - extractOrgSlugFromEndpoint + regex constants
   - orgScopedRequestPaginated
   - orgScopedPaginateAll

### What stays unchanged

- unwrapResult / unwrapPaginatedResult / parseLinkHeader
- apiRequestToRegion (still needed for internal/undocumented endpoints)
- listTeams non-paginated / listProjectTeams (already used SDK correctly)

### Note on per_page

The OpenAPI spec only added cursor; per_page is not yet declared in the types.
Cast query to { cursor?: string } to satisfy TypeScript while passing per_page
at runtime (Sentry's pagination framework reads it from request.GET regardless).
